As I created it in [StackOverflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/62235319/reportprogress-is-not-working-in-production), I'll write it here: 
When I'm uploading video file, it works normally on local (develop mode). But when i'm uploading it to the server (prod), it doesn't work.
Here is the service:
```
uploadVideo(id: String, file, imageId) {
        let formData = new FormData();
        formData.append('video', file);
        formData.append('imageId', imageId);
        return this.http.post<any>(`.../${id}/video`, formData, {reportProgress: true, observe: 'events'})
                .pipe(map(response => {
                        console.log('event', event)
                        return response;
                }));
    }
```
Here is the component:
```
this.arrivalProductService.uploadVideo(this.data.id, this.selectedFile, imageId)
      .pipe(
        map((event) => {
          console.log('event', event);
          if(event.type === HttpEventType.UploadProgress){
            const percentDone = Math.round(100 * event.loaded / event.total);
            return { status: 'progress', message: percentDone };
          }
          if (event.type === HttpEventType.Response) {
            return event.body;
          }
        }),
        catchError(error => {
          return throwError(error);
        }),
        finalize(() => {
          console.log('completed');
        })
      )
      .subscribe(
        data => {
          console.log('data', data)
          ....
       })
```
If I'm logging event on map(), on local dev it returns all types and works perfectly, on production it returns all other types except 'type: 1', which is UploadProgress.
**I tested with:**
1. Same functions by [tutorial](https://angular.io/guide/http#listening-to-progress-events), same issue (works in dev build, doesn't work in prod build)
2. I uploaded dev build to the server where was prod build... dev build works perfectly, prod build - no (so it's not server's issue)

